main event: A visual observation of an unidentified object was made at West Mesa AFS on November 6, 1937.
interesting points: The object was observed at azimuth 230 degrees and a range of over 10 miles., The length of the observation was reported to be 1 minute., The unidentified object was suspected to be an aircraft due to the lack of confirmation., The speed of the object was clocked at high speed by radar., No photographs were included in the report.
location: West Mesa AFS, New Mexico, USA
